      <h1>Charter</h1>
      <p>
        Thanks for your interest in Scotland’s Digital Participation Charter!
      </p>
      <p>
        The Charter has been the focal point for Scotland’s digital inclusion work, bringing together organisations across sectors to work towards a common goal: skilling up our digital nation.
      </p>
      <p>
        It’s important that the Charter continues to reflect and anticipate the changing needs of organisations and individuals engaging in digital inclusion work, and that’s why we’re taking this opportunity to update the Charter based on our learning and conversations since 2021.
      </p>
      <p>
        From the end of December 2023, we will no longer be accepting new Charter signatories as we prepare to launch the refreshed Digital Inclusion Charter for Scotland. Keep an eye on this page in early 2024 for more details.
      </p>
      <p>
        We hope you’re as excited as we are about this: making sure Scotland continues to be a leader in supporting people to access the benefits of the internet.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you have any questions, please don’t hesitate to <a href="mailto:digital@scvo.scot">get in touch with us</a>. We’d love to talk to you about Scotland’s new Charter.
      </p>
      <p>
        Thanks again for your support towards a more digitally inclusive Scotland.
      </p>

